              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4009947-anthony?shelf=modern-english-lit">modern-english-lit</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4044964380" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18287048127401827536">While it doesn’t reach the astounding depths of le Carré’s masterpiece The Spy Who Came in from the Cold, this novel, his first, nonetheless displays his gifts for giving us a subtle, mesmerizing, disturbing glimpse into the murky, cold-blooded world of espionage. And it introduces to the world the peculiar, brilliant, bespectacled spy George Smiley. I look forward to continuing to read his exploits, and I’m grateful that there are many more of them that le Carré wrote. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


